channel.title: Error: Unpacking Config 86
channel.description:
Right, i attempted adding the real Godsword specs to my client (Very basic Galkons Base Source), I got the cases in class23, compiled, all good, But, when i run the client, it gets up to "Unpacking config".
Then it comes up with the error, "Sorry an error has ocurred whilst loading .... Client " On a black screen.
Then when i go to the CMD for the client run, its say exactly "Error: loaderror Unpacking config 86"
I Assure you, when i release this client, it will be ONE of the best clients out so far, as i'm not a nooby little leecher, who can't actually add models and just leeches other clients. I can do that.
Anyways, Anyone got any ideas?
Thanxx

item.dc:creator: @JuzEh JuzEh
item.description:
@JuzEh wrote:

Damn you m.dog311, beat me too it

But I’ll post anyway!

It’s probably the int newSpotAnimCount thing, I’ve gotten this a few times and this always fixes it. Count how many GFX’s you got in class23 and change that number to how many you have.

	        }
	        int newSpotAnimCount = 6;
	        /* Yarnova: Raise this by one every time you add a new GFX */
